<h4>2.2.2 Edit Courses </h4>
<p>When the admin clicks the <b>Courses</b> item under the <b>Databases</b> dropdown, the scheduling program shows the following screen.</p>
<div>
    <a href="images/desk_manage_courses_empty.png"><img src="images/desk_manage_courses_empty.png" width="500px" /></a>
    <p class="caption">Figure 2.2.2-1 shows a list of the courses in the courses database.</p>
</div>
<p>Initially, the list of courses will be empty. To add a course, an admin clicks on <b>Add</b>. The scheduler program opens the following dialog after the admin clicks <b>Add</b>.</p>
<div>
    <a href="images/desk_manage_courses_add_edit_empty.png"><img src="images/desk_manage_courses_add_edit_empty.png" width="500px" /></a>
    <p class="caption">Figure 2.2.2-2a shows the Add/Edit dialog.</p>
</div>
<div>
    <a href="images/desk_manage_courses_add_edit_empty_filled.png"><img src="images/desk_manage_courses_add_edit_empty_filled.png" width="500px" /></a>
    <p class="caption">Figure 2.2.2-2b shows a filled in version of the dialog.</p>
</div>
<p>From here, the admin inputs the course information and clicks <b>Submit</b>. After submitting the information, the scheduler adds the course to the database of courses.</p>
<div>
    <a href="images/desk_manage_courses_one.png"><img src="images/desk_manage_courses_one.png" width="500px" /></a>
    <p class="caption">Figure 2.2.2-3 shows the list of courses with one course in it.</p>
</div>
<p>To add another, the admin must repeat the same steps.</p>
<div>
    <a href="images/desk_manage_courses_two.png"><img src="images/desk_manage_courses_two.png" width="500px" /></a>
    <p class="caption">Figure 2.2.2-4 shows the list of courses with one more course in it.</p>
</div>
<p>The table sorts the courses by their course numbers first, and then their prefixes.</p>
<p>The admin then repeats the steps to completely populate the database.</p>
<div>
    <a href="images/desk_manage_courses.png"><img src="images/desk_manage_courses.png" width="500px" /></a>
    <p class="caption">Figure 2.2.2-5 shows a populated available course list.</p>
</div>
